<title type="html"><![CDATA[Use case for video controls defined by developers.]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=4303&amp;p=5951#p5951"><![CDATA[
If you had a video running, like an ad,  you might want the user to be able to alter the volume based on their computer's volume settings, but not turn it off.  There are many cases where you'd want to limit but not fully get rid of the controls. <br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>&lt;video&gt;Sorry&lt;/video&gt;//Without controls<br />&lt;video controls='all'&gt;Sorry&lt;/video&gt;//Full controls<br />&lt;video controls='volume'&gt;Sorry&lt;/video&gt;//Only volume controls<br />&lt;video controls='allButStop'&gt;Sorry&lt;/video&gt;//All controls except Stop<br />&lt;video controls='mute'&gt;Sorry&lt;/video&gt;//Only muting controls<br /></code></dd></dl><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1245">AMWJ</a> — Mon Jun 14, 2010 8:23 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
