<title type="html"><![CDATA[Stop button for HTML5]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=4303&amp;p=5946#p5946"><![CDATA[
This is good advice for the user agent developer, such as Mozilla, Google, or Microsoft.  The WHATWG specifications don't detail which controls are built into the video players.<br /><br />Although, developers should be able to specify which controls are available to the user, like <dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>volume=&quot;disabled&quot;</code></dd></dl> or <dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>controls=&quot;mute&quot;</code></dd></dl> (to only allow muting).  All or nothing controls seems rather limited.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1245">AMWJ</a> — Sun Jun 13, 2010 11:20 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
